properties.sfomuseum:description: a. Airmail flight cover, Pan American Airways, first scheduled airmail flight between the United States and Manila, San Francisco (Alameda) - Manila leg; green stamped cachet at left, “First flight trans-Pacific; San Francisco to Manila”; postmarked San Francisco, Calif., November 22, 1935 in San Francisco with four-bar cancellation over three 25-cent stamps; backstamp: November 29, 1935, Manila; .b. Backing sheet with two sets of mounting corners, with handwritten caption: “November 1935, Pan American’s inauguration of regular service - San Francisco to Manila”, and black and white photographic image of Pan American China Clipper over Golden Gate Bridge.
